This paper deals with sentiment analysis of financial news headlines, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP, information retrieval, and text analysis. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and word embeddings, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed architecture was evaluated in the context of the SemEval 2017 challenge, which is a shared task in NLP. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
